---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import CalloutBox from '@/components/CalloutBox.astro'
import LearnMoreButton from '../LearnMoreButton.astro'
import HorizonalList from '@/components/HorizontalList.astro';
import HorizonalListItem from '@/components/HorizontalListItem.astro';
---
<section class="mt-3 mb-5">
  <h3>Introducing Phaeno's PSeq<sup class="text-[0.6em] relative -top-3">™</sup> RUO Service</h3>
  <div>
    <CalloutBox 
      bgColor="#545458" 
    >
      <h3 class="text-white text-center">Phaeno has developed a best in class full-length, isoform-resolved<br />transcriptome sequencing service, called PSeq.</h3>      
    </CalloutBox>    
    <h4>
      Information generated by PSeq provides a trove of information for machine learning, described in four
      dimensions.
    </h4>      
    <HorizonalList columns={[1, 1, 2, 2]}>
      <HorizonalListItem>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Image alt="first" height={45} width={45} src="/images/step-1.webp" />
          <div class="text-lg"><b>Scale</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-ml-container">
          From RNAs from single cells to bulk RNAs (&gt;10<sup>9</sup> molecules) to evaluate drug target diversity.
        </div>          
      </HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Image alt="second" height={45} width={45} src="/images/step-2.webp" />
          <div class="text-lg"><b>Depth</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-ml-container">
          How far into an RNA population the technology can penetrate without missing rare isoforms or producing false positives (artifacts). 
          Depth is measured in orders of magnitude of copy number abundance.
        </div>          
      </HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Image alt="third" height={45} width={45} src="/images/step-3.webp" />
          <div class="text-lg"><b>Breadth</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-ml-container">
          The linear combinations of informational elements in each individual messenger RNA, e.g., alternative ORFs, isoform-specific 
          RNA trafficking codes, ribozymes, metabolite-sensing riboswitches, enzyme system-specific pathways for translation activation 
          and transcript-specific degradation, and indicators for isoform-specific promoter, silencer or enhancer gene segments.
        </div>
      </HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Image alt="fourth" height={45} width={45} src="/images/step-4.webp" />
          <div class="text-lg"><b>“Recursion”</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-ml-container">
          Mutual information in mRNA  transcriptome encompasses recursive correlations, such as those between splice variants of transcription 
          factors for splicing regulatory factors, between transcription factor splice variants and down-stream activated genes that, in turn, 
          are alternatively spliced. This vast recursive information, for every active gene, is embodied in the mRNA transcriptome.
        </div>          
      </HorizonalListItem>
    </HorizonalList>
    <h4>Available information</h4>
    <HorizonalList columns={[1, 2, 2, 4]}>
      <HorizonalListItem>ORF-constitutive and alternative protein-coding exons</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Alternative translation initiation sites</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Alternative polyadenylation (chain termination) sites</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>RNA trafficking “zip” codes</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Destination-specific sequences for translation activation pathways</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Metabolite responsive riboswitches</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Intramolecularly directed ribozymes</HorizonalListItem>
      <HorizonalListItem>Multiple consensus domains for local, alternative RNA degradation pathways</HorizonalListItem>
    </HorizonalList>
    <br />    
  </div>
  <LearnMoreButton 
  link="/technology"
  ariaLabel="Learn more about Phaeno's technology and how it addess the shortcoming of genomic analysis" 
  />    

  {(import.meta.env.PUBLIC_HIDE_PSEQ_AVAIL_NOW === "false") && (
    <br />
    <CalloutBox bgColor="var(--home-available-now-bg)">
      <h3 class="mb-3">
        <b>PSeq is available NOW as an RUO<sup>*</sup> service</b>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm"><sup>*</sup><i>RUO - Research use only</i></p>
      </h3>
      <div class="text-black font-bold text-lg mb-1">Service Includes:</div>
      <ul class="service-includes gap-2">
        <li>Samples (tissue or RNA samples) are prepared using our PSeq patiented chemistry.</li>
        <li>Samples are sequenced, and data assembled using our proprietary software.</li>
        <li>Data files and analysis are prepared and delivered per <b>your specifications.</b></li>
        <li>Most samples can be turned around within <b>10 days</b> of receipt.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <div class="buttons-container mt-5">
        <div class="button-container">
          <LearnMoreButton 
            link="/home/ruo-service"
            ariaLabel="Get more details about Phaeno's PSeq RUO service." 
            fullWidth={true}
          />
        </div>
        <div class="button-container">
          <LearnMoreButton 
            link="/home/ruo-service/place-order" 
            label="Order NOW!" 
            ariaLabel="Place a PSeq RUO order." 
            fullWidth={true}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </CalloutBox>
  )}
</section>

<style>
  .section-container {
    display: grid;
    flex-direction: row;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pseq-service-container {
    background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236);
    padding: 5px 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  
  .buttons-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    justify-content: end;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  
  .button-container {
    max-width: 20rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .section-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }  

  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .buttons-container {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-end;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      gap: 8px;
    }
    .button-container {
      max-width: 10rem;
    }    
  }  

  ul {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;    
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }  

  ul.service-includes {
    color: black;
    gap: 1.2rem;    
  }   
</style>